WEBVTT

00:00.453 --> 00:01.851
<i>Previously on "The Rookie"...</i>
I'm pregnant.

00:01.851 --> 00:02.978
I can't tell
if you're joking.
I'm not.

00:02.978 --> 00:03.980
When I get
my license back, I might --

00:03.980 --> 00:06.360
You want to do even more
pro bono work.

00:06.360 --> 00:08.572
Sgt. Grey: Rosalind Dyer,
female serial killer.

00:08.572 --> 00:09.908
Lucy. Caleb.
Hey.

00:09.908 --> 00:11.161
Lucy: You put something
in my drink.

00:11.161 --> 00:12.245
Shh, shh,
shh, shh, shh.

00:12.245 --> 00:13.873
I've got her!
[ Grunts ]

00:13.873 --> 00:16.128
Rosalind: You think the camera
in the barrel was for Caleb?

00:16.128 --> 00:20.011
♪ Stars shining
bright above you ♪

00:26.523 --> 00:30.989
7-Adam-15, show me Code 6
on a single vehicle TC.

00:34.454 --> 00:37.544
Hey. I'm John.

00:37.544 --> 00:39.422
I'm here to help.

00:39.422 --> 00:40.967
What's your name?

00:40.967 --> 00:43.430
I-I-I'm Riley.
Templeton.

00:43.430 --> 00:45.183
[ Siren wails in distance ]

00:45.183 --> 00:47.312
I-I can't find
my ph-phone.

00:47.312 --> 00:48.982
It --

00:48.982 --> 00:50.944
I need to
call my husband.

00:50.944 --> 00:53.115
There's frozen food
in the tr-trunk.

00:53.115 --> 00:54.534
Okay, well,
let's worry about

00:54.534 --> 00:56.329
getting you out of
this car first, okay?

00:56.329 --> 00:58.249
Hey, this is Riley.

00:58.249 --> 01:00.170
We need to get
her out of there fast.

01:03.801 --> 01:06.431
That's a catastrophic
injury.

01:06.431 --> 01:08.769
Riley, we're gonna get this door
open for you, okay?

01:08.769 --> 01:10.481
And John's gonna sit in here
while we do.

01:17.452 --> 01:19.498
Hey. I'm just gonna
keep you company, alright?

01:19.498 --> 01:21.460
Okay.
Okay, yeah.

01:21.460 --> 01:23.130
Hang on.
Okay. Come here.

01:23.130 --> 01:24.507
Don't look at that.
Don't look at that.

01:24.507 --> 01:26.344
Look at me.
Focus on me right now.

01:26.344 --> 01:28.139
Uh, tell me
about your husband.

01:28.139 --> 01:29.892
What's his name?

01:29.892 --> 01:32.231
Harry.
Harry.

01:32.231 --> 01:34.818
He's gonna be so upset.

01:34.818 --> 01:37.365
He loved this car.
[ Breathing shakily ]

01:37.365 --> 01:40.788
At least we have g-g-good
insur-insurance.

01:40.788 --> 01:43.000
No, he's not
gonna be mad at all.

01:43.000 --> 01:46.298
It was just an accident.
It happens to everyone.

01:46.298 --> 01:48.761
And...what about
your kids?

01:48.761 --> 01:50.515
Tell me about them.

01:50.515 --> 01:53.061
We have one.

01:53.061 --> 01:56.192
Royce.
Oh.

01:56.192 --> 02:00.700
H-His P-Popsicles are melting
in the tr-trunk.

02:00.700 --> 02:03.873
Oh, listen, I-I'm gonna make
sure he gets new ones, okay?

02:03.873 --> 02:07.505
So you don't have
to worry about that.

02:07.505 --> 02:11.262
You're a very nice man,
John.

02:11.262 --> 02:13.850
P-Please don't
give me a ticket.

02:13.850 --> 02:15.896
I-I-I'm really sorry.

02:15.896 --> 02:18.317
Riley, you are
not getting a ticket.

02:19.569 --> 02:22.575
Hey, Riley,
you stay with me, okay?

02:22.575 --> 02:25.039
[ Choking ]
Riley?

02:25.039 --> 02:26.458
Riley.

02:26.458 --> 02:33.471
♪♪

02:33.471 --> 02:36.184
Bailey.

02:36.184 --> 02:40.108
Uh...she's, um...

02:40.108 --> 02:46.662
♪♪

02:46.662 --> 02:48.791
You wanna call it?

02:51.797 --> 02:54.468
Yeah. Uh...

02:54.468 --> 02:56.055
9:38.

02:56.055 --> 02:58.059
Is she a donor?

02:58.059 --> 02:59.687
Uh...

03:04.320 --> 03:06.199
Yeah. She is.

03:06.199 --> 03:07.827
You guys wanna arrange
transport?

03:07.827 --> 03:09.247
Yeah.
I'll get it started.

03:10.874 --> 03:14.548
Control, Engine 113.
We have one victim, 10-5-5.

03:14.548 --> 03:17.053
Advise Shaw Memorial
we're transporting a donor.

03:17.053 --> 03:20.059
ETA six minutes,
9:38 hours.

03:20.059 --> 03:21.686
Details on the box.

03:21.686 --> 03:23.898
[ Sighs ] Oh, God.

03:23.898 --> 03:27.031
♪ Could this be the last time ♪

03:27.031 --> 03:30.745
♪ I see your face in person? ♪

03:30.745 --> 03:34.210
♪ We sleep until the daylight ♪

03:34.210 --> 03:37.800
♪ Open all the curtains ♪

03:37.800 --> 03:41.515
♪ Paint the morning heaven's
colors ♪

03:41.515 --> 03:45.607
♪ Drive all day to see it ♪

03:45.607 --> 03:47.360
I'm Dr. Spader.

03:47.360 --> 03:49.405
Were you able to talk to
the victim before she died?

03:49.405 --> 03:50.992
Yeah.
Her name is Riley.

03:50.992 --> 03:52.828
<i>Was.</i> Was Riley.

03:52.828 --> 03:54.624
W-What are they doing?

03:54.624 --> 03:56.252
It's an Honor Walk.

03:56.252 --> 03:58.839
Our way of showing respect
for organ donors.

03:58.839 --> 04:00.176
Are you gonna be
around for a while?

04:00.176 --> 04:01.470
I have some questions.

04:01.470 --> 04:03.265
Yeah.
Great.

04:03.265 --> 04:06.980
♪♪

04:06.980 --> 04:10.362
♪ Could this be
the first time ♪

04:10.362 --> 04:13.868
♪ I see you breaking down? ♪

04:13.868 --> 04:17.542
♪ Ooh ♪

04:21.842 --> 04:25.056
Lopez:
I know it's daunting rebuilding
your law practice from scratch,

04:25.056 --> 04:27.769
but I made you these
fancy cards,

04:27.769 --> 04:29.773
so why you sweating?

04:29.773 --> 04:31.235
[ Chuckles ]

04:31.235 --> 04:32.445
They are nice.

04:32.445 --> 04:33.906
Wesley Evers,
Attorney At Law.

04:33.906 --> 04:35.033
Total Hunk.

04:35.033 --> 04:36.786
That last part's subtext.

04:36.786 --> 04:38.081
[ Chuckles ]

04:38.081 --> 04:40.169
Don't get me wrong,
they're great,

04:40.169 --> 04:43.090
and I'm thrilled to finally
get my license back,

04:43.090 --> 04:46.513
but I have zero clients,
and no clients are lining up

04:46.513 --> 04:48.767
to hire a lawyer that was just
disciplined by the State Bar.

04:48.767 --> 04:51.689
Your client base is
sleazebags -- no offense.

04:51.689 --> 04:53.026
I think you're
gonna be fine.

04:53.026 --> 04:54.361
Oh, the entire
criminal underworld knows

04:54.361 --> 04:55.990
that I dropped a dime
on Elijah.

04:55.990 --> 04:58.203
I'll be lucky if they let me
handle their parking tickets.

04:58.203 --> 04:59.871
Then find a better
brand of clientele.

04:59.871 --> 05:01.124
You mean richer.

05:01.124 --> 05:02.877
Of course I do.

05:02.877 --> 05:05.841
Rich people commit hella crimes,
and Mama needs a vacation house.

05:05.841 --> 05:07.220
Mm.

05:07.220 --> 05:10.058
I was actually thinking about
advertising to get new clients.

05:10.058 --> 05:12.562
Alright, picture this --
buses, subways.

05:12.562 --> 05:14.358
A sign with
my face on it.

05:14.358 --> 05:18.823
And next to it,
"Best. Lawyer. Evers."

05:18.823 --> 05:20.494
Go away.

05:20.494 --> 05:21.956
I'm gonna take that
as an endorsement.

05:21.956 --> 05:23.625
I think you like that.

05:23.625 --> 05:26.172
[ Sizzling ]

05:26.172 --> 05:28.092
What's that smell?

05:28.092 --> 05:30.304
That depends.
Does it smell good?

05:30.304 --> 05:32.600
Uh, it smells delicious.

05:32.600 --> 05:33.727
Then it's your breakfast.

05:33.727 --> 05:35.355
Ooh.

05:35.355 --> 05:38.946
It's a Pop Tart
egg sandwich?

05:38.946 --> 05:40.615
I saw it on ClipTalk.
Oh.

05:40.615 --> 05:44.372
Historically not my favorite
recipes, but, uh...

05:45.749 --> 05:47.003
Mm-hmm.

05:47.003 --> 05:49.215
♪ 'Cause I dance
when I'm feeling funky ♪

05:49.215 --> 05:50.759
♪ But I'm
lost in a crowded room ♪

05:50.759 --> 05:51.929
Mm.

05:51.929 --> 05:53.015
♪ I hate this view ♪

05:53.015 --> 05:54.516
Okay.

05:54.516 --> 05:57.230
That is a unique experience,
but it's not bad.

05:57.230 --> 05:58.733
What's all
the fuss about?

05:58.733 --> 06:00.403
I just want today
to go well for you.

06:00.403 --> 06:03.825
I appreciate that,
but it's gonna be fine.

06:03.825 --> 06:05.537
It just seems so unnecessary
to dig through

06:05.537 --> 06:07.374
the worst moments of your life
just so the D. A.

06:07.374 --> 06:09.295
can slap a few charges
on Rosalind Dyer.

06:09.295 --> 06:11.966
All the D. A. needs me to do
is tell them

06:11.966 --> 06:13.427
everything that happened
so they can prove

06:13.427 --> 06:15.473
Rosalind was an accessory
in Caleb's crimes.

06:15.473 --> 06:17.435
It's a story I've told
my therapist a hundred times.

06:17.435 --> 06:18.687
But is it worth it

06:18.687 --> 06:21.359
when she's already serving
four life sentences?

06:21.359 --> 06:25.910
It's important that she's held
accountable for every crime.

06:25.910 --> 06:28.331
Most of her victims
are dead.

06:28.331 --> 06:30.334
I'm fortunate to be
able to do so.

06:30.334 --> 06:32.380
Okay.
But I'm coming with.

06:32.380 --> 06:33.966
I'll have snacks in my bag

06:33.966 --> 06:35.803
and puppy videos on my phone
for when you need them.

06:35.803 --> 06:37.682
Thank you.

06:37.682 --> 06:40.603
You're the first person
I've ever heard of

06:40.603 --> 06:43.567
who brings their own sheets
to the hospital.

06:43.567 --> 06:45.989
Look, if we are gonna be hanging
around a hospital all day

06:45.989 --> 06:48.743
waiting on tests, then we
might as well do it in style.

06:48.743 --> 06:51.833
Okay, my girl Lisa got us
this private room.

06:51.833 --> 06:54.630
They are serving pizza
in the cafeteria.

06:54.630 --> 06:55.883
It's a great day.

06:55.883 --> 06:57.510
I don't know.
I wouldn't go that far.

07:00.892 --> 07:03.730
Okay. Look at me.

07:03.730 --> 07:04.900
Okay?

07:04.900 --> 07:09.533
Yes, I had a little bleeding
this morning,

07:09.533 --> 07:15.794
but...we're here now,
and all we can do is wait

07:15.794 --> 07:17.756
for my lab work
to finish up.

07:17.756 --> 07:19.093
I get that.

07:19.093 --> 07:21.055
And I'm not worried --

07:21.055 --> 07:23.434
No, you just don't like
hospitals.

07:23.434 --> 07:25.104
No one does.

07:25.104 --> 07:28.611
Avoiding medical care is just
such a male instinct.

07:28.611 --> 07:30.573
Mm, I'm not avoiding.
Mm.

07:30.573 --> 07:32.117
I'm just healthy.

07:32.117 --> 07:34.455
When is the last time
you got a complete physical?

07:34.455 --> 07:36.334
Seeing the way you're
looking at me right now,

07:36.334 --> 07:38.881
I-I think I'm gonna refrain
from answering that one.

07:41.301 --> 07:43.890
Fine. Uh, six years.

07:43.890 --> 07:46.102
Thank you, Officer.
Tim: Yeah.

07:46.102 --> 07:48.900
My daughter Piper is
getting a new heart today.

07:48.900 --> 07:50.610
Dad.
What?

07:50.610 --> 07:52.864
We thought this day
would never come, right?

07:52.864 --> 07:54.785
Well, I'd say congratulations,
but that seems like

07:54.785 --> 07:56.163
too small a sentiment.

07:56.163 --> 07:57.749
How about "Thank God"?

07:57.749 --> 07:59.044
Amen.

07:59.044 --> 08:00.587
[ Chuckles ]

08:00.587 --> 08:04.303
♪♪

08:04.303 --> 08:08.143
Dr. Spader: It's one of
Mrs. Templeton's kidneys.

08:08.143 --> 08:10.147
Headed to Oklahoma.

08:10.147 --> 08:12.903
That's something you
don't see every day.

08:12.903 --> 08:14.614
Well, unless you're you.

08:14.614 --> 08:15.993
I mean...

08:15.993 --> 08:17.786
are all Riley's organs
going somewhere else?

08:17.786 --> 08:20.584
No, I'm transplanting
her heart this afternoon.

08:20.584 --> 08:22.170
I have a few questions
for you.

08:22.170 --> 08:25.051
Was Riley conscious when
you arrived at the scene?

08:25.051 --> 08:27.221
Yeah, as a matter of fact,
she was talking

08:27.221 --> 08:28.891
right up until
the moment she passed.

08:28.891 --> 08:30.561
Was she making sense?

08:30.561 --> 08:32.148
Well, she was in shock.

08:32.148 --> 08:36.280
Had no idea how serious
the accident was, but yeah.

08:36.280 --> 08:38.994
She was worried her husband
would be mad about the car.

08:38.994 --> 08:40.371
Hmm.

08:40.371 --> 08:41.916
Do you have any reason
to suspect that

08:41.916 --> 08:44.462
she was under the influence
of alcohol or drugs?

08:44.462 --> 08:45.672
No.

08:45.672 --> 08:47.509
Okay. Good.

08:47.509 --> 08:49.555
Good luck today.
Thanks, Officer.

08:49.555 --> 08:51.559
Excuse me.
I have to go meet my patient.

08:51.559 --> 08:52.896
Of course.

08:53.729 --> 08:55.107
Tim: Hey.

08:55.107 --> 08:57.195
Heard your fatal this morning
was a rough one.

08:57.195 --> 08:58.864
Yeah.

08:58.864 --> 09:01.703
Well, that girl is getting
a new heart because of it,

09:01.703 --> 09:05.418
so hold on to that
silver lining if you can.

09:05.418 --> 09:07.381
Her dad said they'd almost
given up hope

09:07.381 --> 09:09.051
that they'd ever
find a match.

09:09.051 --> 09:11.513
Guess she has
a rare blood type.

09:11.513 --> 09:14.018
As a parent,
there is nothing scarier

09:14.018 --> 09:16.481
than being unable
to help your child.

09:16.481 --> 09:19.153
Well, today is
their lucky day.

09:23.577 --> 09:24.872
[ Exhales sharply ]

09:24.872 --> 09:26.918
Um, I'm gonna
hit the restroom.

09:26.918 --> 09:28.045
Do you want me
to come with you?

09:28.045 --> 09:29.672
[ Scoffs ]
I think I can handle it.

09:29.672 --> 09:31.509
Will you let them know
that I'm here?

09:31.509 --> 09:33.430
Sure.
Okay.

09:37.438 --> 09:40.735
[ Breathing heavily ]

09:52.466 --> 09:53.969
Rock, Paper, Scissors?

09:53.969 --> 09:56.264
You should
definitely go first.

09:56.264 --> 09:57.850
I have a tendency to
fold under pressure.

09:57.850 --> 09:59.145
[ Chuckles ]

10:01.649 --> 10:03.779
Do you work here?
You look my age.

10:03.779 --> 10:07.327
Oh, I'm a college intern.
Environmental Crime Unit.

10:07.327 --> 10:09.164
Oh, cool.
What kind of cases do you do?

10:09.164 --> 10:11.627
Well, water pollution,
mostly.

10:11.627 --> 10:13.506
[ Chuckles ]

10:13.506 --> 10:15.092
I don't want to boast,
but I'm actually

10:15.092 --> 10:17.179
single-handedly
saving the Earth.

10:17.179 --> 10:18.848
And you're
only an intern?

10:18.848 --> 10:20.852
I mean, you might want to talk
to somebody about that.

10:20.852 --> 10:21.854
Right?

10:21.854 --> 10:23.107
[ Chuckles ]

10:23.107 --> 10:24.985
Oh, uh, I gotta go.

10:24.985 --> 10:28.117
It was
nice meeting you.
Yeah. You -- You, too.

10:28.117 --> 10:30.037
Oh. Hey.

10:30.037 --> 10:31.581
Hi.
Hey.

10:31.581 --> 10:33.167
Um, d-do you know
where Sarah is?

10:33.167 --> 10:34.753
I-I'm here
for trial prep.

10:34.753 --> 10:36.298
I know.
She's out sick.

10:36.298 --> 10:37.592
Oh.

10:37.592 --> 10:39.763
They asked me to step in,
but that seems awkward,

10:39.763 --> 10:41.474
given our relationship.

10:41.474 --> 10:42.768
I say we reschedule.

10:42.768 --> 10:46.192
No.
Um...we're professionals.

10:46.192 --> 10:48.530
We're just discussing
the details of the case.

10:48.530 --> 10:49.740
It'll -- It'll be fine.

10:49.740 --> 10:52.287
Okay.
Um, let's get to it.

10:52.287 --> 10:53.831
Mm.

10:54.959 --> 10:56.628
Okay, sorry to
keep you waiting.

10:56.628 --> 10:57.923
It's been
a crazy morning.

10:57.923 --> 11:00.343
Test results are in,
and [sighs]

11:00.343 --> 11:02.181
I'm so sorry to have to
tell you this,

11:02.181 --> 11:04.602
but it looks like you
have prostate cancer.

11:04.602 --> 11:06.940
Oh.
You're not Mr. Johnson.

11:06.940 --> 11:09.360
Oh, no, no.
I am not.

11:09.360 --> 11:10.738
Is this Room 516 East?

11:10.738 --> 11:12.241
It is.
Mm-hmm.

11:12.241 --> 11:13.953
I'm so sorry.

11:13.953 --> 11:16.124
It looks like there's something
amiss with our system.

11:16.124 --> 11:18.753
Well, better the system
than my prostate.

11:18.753 --> 11:21.008
We have a psychologist
on standby

11:21.008 --> 11:22.552
if you need to
talk to someone.

11:22.552 --> 11:24.891
This qualifies as Critical
Incident Stress Debriefing,

11:24.891 --> 11:26.936
so there's
no charge to you.

11:26.936 --> 11:28.271
I think
I'll be alright.

11:28.271 --> 11:30.692
[ Alarm blaring ]

11:32.655 --> 11:34.951
What's going on?
I don't know.

11:34.951 --> 11:36.828
Our system is showing that
we have patients coding

11:36.828 --> 11:38.707
in every room on this floor.

11:38.707 --> 11:40.544
Gotta be a glitch, right?
A short?

11:40.544 --> 11:43.384
No, it's not a glitch
or a short.

11:43.384 --> 11:45.512
How do you know?
Because it's me.

11:45.512 --> 11:49.270
I've taken over
the entire network.

11:49.270 --> 11:50.605
And the backup servers.

11:50.605 --> 11:52.276
I have total control
of this hospital.

11:52.276 --> 11:53.610
And what is it
you want?

11:53.610 --> 11:56.199
♪♪

11:56.199 --> 11:57.785
Riley Templeton's heart.

11:57.785 --> 11:59.622
And if my wife
doesn't get the heart,

11:59.622 --> 12:03.045
I'm gonna start shutting down
every system in this hospital,

12:03.045 --> 12:04.589
and people start dying.

12:10.809 --> 12:12.771
Nolan: Here she is.
Where's the guy?

12:12.771 --> 12:14.525
Jonah Russell is cuffed
and in a conference room.

12:14.525 --> 12:16.195
An officer's watching him.

12:16.195 --> 12:17.949
His wife, Meredith, is in
a patient room being examined.

12:17.949 --> 12:19.452
She's in
pretty bad shape.

12:19.452 --> 12:22.206
This is Linda Brooks.
She runs the hospital.

12:22.206 --> 12:24.627
Detective Lopez. I'll be
spearheading the investigation.

12:24.627 --> 12:26.131
Can you give me
a status report?

12:26.131 --> 12:28.052
We got the alarms
turned off manually,

12:28.052 --> 12:30.221
and we're canceling all
non-essential procedures,

12:30.221 --> 12:32.935
but a full-scale evacuation
would be a massive undertaking.

12:32.935 --> 12:34.730
And we have critical-care
patients

12:34.730 --> 12:36.067
who won't survive
being moved.

12:36.067 --> 12:38.070
Evacuation's
the last resort.

12:38.070 --> 12:40.407
I have our Cyber Crimes Unit
working with your IT head,

12:40.407 --> 12:42.411
so hopefully, they can find
a way to force the guy out

12:42.411 --> 12:43.915
before
anything else happens.

12:43.915 --> 12:46.127
While we're waiting on that,
take a run at the husband.

12:46.127 --> 12:47.880
See what kind of guy
we're dealing with.

12:47.880 --> 12:49.091
Talk to the wife.

12:49.091 --> 12:50.718
Use that Midwestern charm
to convince her

12:50.718 --> 12:52.932
to stop her husband from
continuing this insanity.

12:52.932 --> 12:55.186
I'm not actually from
the Midwest, but I'll...

12:55.186 --> 12:57.356
[ Monitor beeping ]

13:00.320 --> 13:02.658
When will they
bring my husband in?

13:02.658 --> 13:03.953
They won't.

13:03.953 --> 13:07.125
He's being questioned pending
arrest, like you are now.

13:07.125 --> 13:10.214
I didn't know Jonah's plan.
I swear.

13:10.214 --> 13:12.301
This morning, he just told me
to get in the car,

13:12.301 --> 13:14.179
said we were going in
for a checkup.

13:15.807 --> 13:18.981
I'm sorry.
For all this mess.

13:18.981 --> 13:22.486
Well, that helps.
A little.

13:22.486 --> 13:25.617
But you're gonna have to do a
lot more than say you're sorry.

13:25.617 --> 13:29.083
You need to convince
your husband to stop this.

13:29.083 --> 13:30.794
Now.

13:30.794 --> 13:32.965
There's 800 patients
in this hospital.

13:32.965 --> 13:34.718
Dozens of them
in critical care.

13:34.718 --> 13:37.599
Every moment that their
treatment is compromised,

13:37.599 --> 13:39.060
any one of them
could die.

13:39.060 --> 13:42.774
He's only doing this
because he loves me.

13:42.774 --> 13:46.616
I have a rare blood type
and I've had cancer.

13:46.616 --> 13:49.288
That's why I'm so low
on the list.

13:49.288 --> 13:53.378
Without a new heart,
I only have a few weeks left.

13:53.378 --> 13:56.259
I-I understand.

13:56.259 --> 13:58.889
I do.

13:58.889 --> 14:03.606
But what your husband is doing
is going to hurt people.

14:03.606 --> 14:05.401
Is your life worth more
than theirs?

14:05.401 --> 14:08.198
No.
No, of course not.

14:08.198 --> 14:11.371
Then you need to
tell Jonah to stop.

14:11.371 --> 14:14.293
♪♪

14:14.293 --> 14:16.089
I don't want to die.

14:17.841 --> 14:20.179
I'm sorry.

14:20.179 --> 14:21.515
Meredith --

14:21.515 --> 14:23.769
I need to rest.

14:23.769 --> 14:25.522
Jonah: Are you prepping
my wife for surgery?

14:25.522 --> 14:27.442
No, and they're
not going to.

14:27.442 --> 14:29.280
You need to
end this now.

14:29.280 --> 14:32.202
As soon as my wife gets
her heart, it all stops.

14:32.202 --> 14:35.165
But if anything happens to her
because you're wasting my time

14:35.165 --> 14:36.793
trying to talk me out of this,
then I'm --

14:36.793 --> 14:38.130
I'm gonna fry
the whole system.

14:38.130 --> 14:39.757
I'm -- I'm gonna kill
this hospital.

14:39.757 --> 14:42.138
Let's dial back
the threats, okay?

14:42.138 --> 14:44.683
So far, all you've really done
is hack the hospital's network

14:44.683 --> 14:46.645
and disrupt
one alarm system.

14:46.645 --> 14:49.651
Now, you cooperate now, charges
against you won't be so bad.

14:49.651 --> 14:53.658
Do you really think that I care
about what happens to me?

14:53.658 --> 14:56.664
Look, my wife has been
my whole life for 30 years,

14:56.664 --> 14:58.376
and for the last two,
I've watched her

14:58.376 --> 15:01.257
get sicker and sicker because
she needs a new heart,

15:01.257 --> 15:05.514
and I-I couldn't
help her.

15:05.514 --> 15:06.767
But now I can.

15:06.767 --> 15:08.228
What time is it?
Why?

15:08.228 --> 15:10.066
Because I need to enter the
abort code into the tablet

15:10.066 --> 15:13.237
by 10:45, otherwise phase two
of the attack begins,

15:13.237 --> 15:16.452
and then people really will,
uh, start to get hurt.

15:16.452 --> 15:18.539
That's in 20 seconds.
What's gonna happen?

15:20.209 --> 15:21.544
You'll see.

15:21.544 --> 15:24.092
[ Keyboard clacking ]

15:24.092 --> 15:25.094
[ Beeping ]

15:25.094 --> 15:26.513
[ Powers down ]

15:26.513 --> 15:28.599
♪♪

15:28.599 --> 15:30.228
What the...

15:30.228 --> 15:32.065
What's going on?

15:32.065 --> 15:34.194
♪♪

15:34.194 --> 15:35.948
[ Beeping ]

15:35.948 --> 15:37.366
What's happening?

15:37.366 --> 15:38.451
Our computers
just locked.

15:38.451 --> 15:39.787
We don't have access
to anything --

15:39.787 --> 15:42.836
patient histories, medication
schedules, doctors' orders.

15:42.836 --> 15:44.797
It's all gone.

15:44.797 --> 15:46.466
Got anything?

15:48.095 --> 15:50.349
Excuse me.
Are you the officer in charge?

15:50.349 --> 15:52.311
I'm Detective Lopez.
How can I help you?

15:52.311 --> 15:55.109
Well, I'm hearing some rumors
that some crazy guy

15:55.109 --> 15:56.485
is trying to
take the heart

15:56.485 --> 15:58.531
that's supposed to go
to my daughter.

15:58.531 --> 16:01.162
I'm sorry to say
you heard right.

16:01.162 --> 16:02.456
You must be Piper.

16:02.456 --> 16:04.126
Yes. Um...

16:04.126 --> 16:06.922
Please, no one will tell us
what's going on.

16:06.922 --> 16:09.135
My daughter has been through
so much already.

16:09.135 --> 16:10.679
We really
deserve some answers.

16:10.679 --> 16:13.267
I'll tell you
what I can say.

16:13.267 --> 16:16.983
A man has hacked into the
hospital computer network,

16:16.983 --> 16:20.531
hoping to force the hospital to
give his wife the donor heart.

16:20.531 --> 16:21.826
You can't let them.

16:21.826 --> 16:23.203
It's not up to me.

16:23.203 --> 16:25.081
It's not up to
the hospital, either.

16:25.081 --> 16:27.044
I'm next on the list.

16:27.044 --> 16:29.673
By law, the hospital has to
give the heart to me.

16:29.673 --> 16:30.675
Do you have a lawyer?

16:30.675 --> 16:32.220
We don't have
money for that.

16:32.220 --> 16:34.390
We spent all our savings
on her care.

16:34.390 --> 16:36.269
I'm not allowed to
make a referral,

16:36.269 --> 16:39.025
but I happen to know
Mr. Evers

16:39.025 --> 16:41.529
has an annoying habit
of working for free.

16:41.529 --> 16:43.825
Did you ever hear Caleb talking
to Rosalind on the phone?

16:43.825 --> 16:46.330
Mm, no.

16:46.330 --> 16:49.044
Did he talk about her
as if they were communicating?

16:49.044 --> 16:51.882
[ Inhales deeply ]
No.

16:51.882 --> 16:55.556
So how can you be sure
he was working with her?

16:55.556 --> 16:56.850
[ Chuckles ]

16:56.850 --> 16:59.187
Becau-- Because she
told me herself

16:59.187 --> 17:00.941
when I visited her
in prison.

17:00.941 --> 17:03.112
She repeated the song
I sang in the barrel.

17:03.112 --> 17:04.614
How -- How would
she know that

17:04.614 --> 17:07.578
if her and Caleb
weren't in communication?

17:07.578 --> 17:10.250
[ Voice fading ] You know
I'm only asking you because...

17:13.924 --> 17:16.511
Lucy.
I just want you to be ready.

17:16.511 --> 17:19.642
I'm familiar with
the concept of trial prep.

17:19.642 --> 17:22.315
I know.

17:22.315 --> 17:25.988
Uh, how about
we take a break?

17:25.988 --> 17:27.073
Yeah.

17:28.743 --> 17:31.081
I could
use some coffee.

17:31.081 --> 17:33.461
Well, you're in luck.

17:33.461 --> 17:35.005
We just got
a new coffee maker.

17:35.005 --> 17:36.341
The old one
took a bullet.

17:36.341 --> 17:37.801
New, huh?

17:37.801 --> 17:39.805
That's pretty fancy
for government work.

17:39.805 --> 17:41.476
Well, new for us.

17:41.476 --> 17:43.980
I'm pretty sure it was born
before we were.

17:43.980 --> 17:45.984
[ Chuckles ]
Come on.

17:45.984 --> 17:51.328
♪♪

17:51.328 --> 17:54.083
Is this food for anybody,
or do you have to work here?

17:54.083 --> 17:57.589
Oh, it's employees only,
but I won't tell.

17:57.589 --> 17:59.928
What do you want?
Whatcha got?

17:59.928 --> 18:01.931
Well, if you
love preservatives,

18:01.931 --> 18:03.225
you've come to
the right place.

18:03.225 --> 18:04.853
Super bad for your health,
though,

18:04.853 --> 18:07.650
and the packaging is
terrible for the planet.

18:07.650 --> 18:08.861
Farming's no better.

18:08.861 --> 18:10.196
If you wanna
get real about it,

18:10.196 --> 18:11.825
you're trading packaging
for fertilizer.

18:11.825 --> 18:14.204
Oh, yeah. And meat's just
antibiotics and methane, so...

18:14.204 --> 18:15.540
[ Both chuckle ]

18:15.540 --> 18:18.462
So, basically, we have to learn
how to live on air.

18:18.462 --> 18:20.632
Ooh,
can I have one?

18:20.632 --> 18:22.302
Sure.

18:22.302 --> 18:23.805
I wondered where you went.

18:23.805 --> 18:26.185
Chris: Two watery coffees,
coming up.

18:26.185 --> 18:27.271
How's it going?

18:27.271 --> 18:28.857
Uh, great.

18:28.857 --> 18:31.028
This is Austin.
He's saving the planet.

18:31.028 --> 18:33.657
Oh. Good to know
someone's doing it.

18:33.657 --> 18:36.705
Um, you can go.
I-I'm fine here.

18:36.705 --> 18:37.957
I don't know.

18:37.957 --> 18:39.836
I'm finding this all
so fascinating.

18:39.836 --> 18:42.842
You know, justice
and laws and stuff.

18:42.842 --> 18:46.598
Uh-huh. And what exactly
is so interesting?

18:46.598 --> 18:47.934
[ Chuckles ]

18:47.934 --> 18:49.437
Chris:
♪ ...you'll miss me ♪

18:49.437 --> 18:52.819
♪ While I'm alone
and blue as can be ♪

18:52.819 --> 18:54.155
You okay?

18:54.155 --> 18:56.200
♪ Dream a little dream... ♪

18:56.200 --> 18:58.955
Lucy: ♪ ...of me ♪

18:58.955 --> 19:01.126
I'm so sorry.

19:01.126 --> 19:03.464
It was in my head.
I wasn't thinking.

19:03.464 --> 19:06.719
I-It was thoughtless and stupid,
and I'm sorry.

19:06.719 --> 19:11.604
The song was stuck
in your head because you've...

19:11.604 --> 19:13.565
because you've
seen the video.

19:13.565 --> 19:16.363
Well, yeah.
It's evidence.

19:16.363 --> 19:18.033
Right, right.
No, of course you did.

19:18.033 --> 19:22.040
You're in the D. A.'s office,
and it's evidence,

19:22.040 --> 19:25.255
so...you've...

19:25.255 --> 19:26.883
Lucy, I should have
told you I'd seen it.

19:26.883 --> 19:28.052
I'm sorry.

19:28.052 --> 19:30.515
No, you said
that part already. Um...

19:30.515 --> 19:32.685
I just --
I just need a minute.

19:32.685 --> 19:33.520
Lucy, p--

19:33.520 --> 19:35.607
Please, can you...

19:35.607 --> 19:37.611
Yeah.

19:41.034 --> 19:42.830
[ Breathing shakily ]

19:42.830 --> 19:44.917
[ Groans ]

19:44.917 --> 19:47.130
Knock, knock.
I have a favor to ask.

19:47.130 --> 19:49.425
Our hospital
social worker's tied up.

19:49.425 --> 19:53.141
Would you mind
keeping an eye on Rory here?

19:53.141 --> 19:54.936
He took a fall
on a field trip.

19:54.936 --> 19:56.857
He seems okay now,
but the E. R. lost power

19:56.857 --> 19:58.442
before
he could be examined.

19:58.442 --> 19:59.820
We're trying to get
in touch with his parents.

19:59.820 --> 20:01.114
Of course.
Bring him in.

20:01.114 --> 20:02.325
Thanks.

20:02.325 --> 20:04.412
Hop on up into bed.

20:06.291 --> 20:07.877
Good.

20:07.877 --> 20:09.338
Okay.

20:09.338 --> 20:11.508
A doctor will be by
to check on him soon.

20:11.508 --> 20:14.014
Hi, Rory.
I'm Nyla Harper.

20:14.014 --> 20:16.476
[ <i>Video game noises</i> ]
This is, um...

20:16.476 --> 20:20.108
Hmm. Well, so much
for a private room.
Mm-hmm.

20:20.108 --> 20:22.279
Sorry, sir.
Right now, we're nowhere.

20:22.279 --> 20:23.698
Jonah's refusing
to back down.

20:23.698 --> 20:24.951
What about the wife?

20:24.951 --> 20:26.286
She knows what
he's doing is wrong,

20:26.286 --> 20:27.664
but is too scared
of dying to stop it.

20:27.664 --> 20:29.209
Any luck with
the Cyber guys?

20:29.209 --> 20:31.380
No, but they've
confirmed that Jonah

20:31.380 --> 20:33.050
has got a stranglehold on
the hospital's network.

20:33.050 --> 20:34.844
Did FEMA get there?
<i>Just landed.</i>

20:34.844 --> 20:36.722
They're talking about
setting up a field hospital

20:36.722 --> 20:37.850
in the parking lot.

20:37.850 --> 20:39.770
Best case --
that takes 24 hours.

20:39.770 --> 20:41.190
We don't have
that kind of time.

20:41.190 --> 20:43.193
Any intel on Jonah
that might help us?

20:43.193 --> 20:45.949
<i>No criminal history.</i>
<i>Master's degree from Cal Poly.</i>

20:45.949 --> 20:48.412
Ran an IT department
for a credit union

20:48.412 --> 20:51.376
until his wife's illness
required full-time care.

20:51.376 --> 20:53.379
What about family?
Anything I can use for leverage?

20:53.379 --> 20:55.174
Anything he cares about
as much as her?

20:55.174 --> 20:57.512
No parents,
no siblings, no kids.

20:57.512 --> 21:00.268
Coworkers describe him
as a loner.

21:00.268 --> 21:04.191
His only police contact
was a 5150 hold in '09

21:04.191 --> 21:06.362
after she threatened
to leave.

21:06.362 --> 21:07.907
She's his whole world.

21:07.907 --> 21:10.745
Great. We should all be so lucky
to have such devotion.

21:10.745 --> 21:13.292
I got a meeting.
[ Sighs ]

21:13.292 --> 21:15.212
Are you still able
to treat patients?

21:15.212 --> 21:16.673
Well, we're using
paper charts for now,

21:16.673 --> 21:18.802
but almost everything
is hooked up to the network --

21:18.802 --> 21:22.142
records, pharmacy,
even surgical equipment.

21:22.142 --> 21:23.770
How long before you
have to make a choice?

21:23.770 --> 21:26.275
A human heart is only viable
for four to six hours

21:26.275 --> 21:28.445
once it's been removed
from a donor's body.

21:28.445 --> 21:30.783
I've already lost
two of those hours.

21:30.783 --> 21:32.578
So, I'm going to get prepped
for surgery,

21:32.578 --> 21:36.294
because I am putting that heart
in someone in an hour.

21:36.294 --> 21:39.216
It's up to you to decide
who my patient will be.

21:39.216 --> 21:41.762
W-- It has to be Piper,
right?

21:41.762 --> 21:44.267
I mean, you can't just decide
who gets an organ.

21:44.267 --> 21:46.687
Excuse me.
I'm Wesley Evers.

21:46.687 --> 21:48.274
I'm representing Graham Scott
and his daughter, Piper.

21:48.274 --> 21:49.652
I need to
speak with you.

21:49.652 --> 21:51.322
Uh, Mr. Evers,
now is not a good time.

21:51.322 --> 21:53.284
Now is the only time.

21:53.284 --> 21:57.041
If your hospital decides to give
in to this terrorist's demands,

21:57.041 --> 21:59.254
to take away the heart that
has been promised to Miss Scott,

21:59.254 --> 22:00.882
that is tantamount to
organ brokering.

22:00.882 --> 22:02.718
If you continue
down this path,

22:02.718 --> 22:04.430
I will file a report
with the medical board,

22:04.430 --> 22:06.350
and you will be st--
Mr. Evers,
let me assure you,

22:06.350 --> 22:09.523
I have no intention of giving in
to Mr. Russell's demands.

22:09.523 --> 22:12.528
[ Alarms blaring ]

22:12.528 --> 22:14.031
Can I get that
in writing?

22:14.031 --> 22:15.409
Nurse Lisa:
Everything's down.

22:15.409 --> 22:17.413
Vents, cardiac monitors,
medicine drips.

22:17.413 --> 22:18.540
Isn't there
a backup generator?

22:18.540 --> 22:20.252
Yeah, but it
isn't coming on.

22:23.674 --> 22:25.511
[ Monitor alarm beeping ]

22:29.686 --> 22:32.232
Help!

22:32.232 --> 22:35.071
I need some help
in here!

22:35.071 --> 22:37.284
Someone! Help!

22:41.124 --> 22:43.420
I need oxygen.
15 liters.

22:43.420 --> 22:50.600
♪♪

22:50.600 --> 22:57.781
♪♪

22:57.781 --> 22:58.908
He's gone.

23:03.583 --> 23:05.964
Meredith Russell gets the heart.
We're prepping the O. R. now.

23:05.964 --> 23:07.757
Absolutely not.
We have no choice.

23:07.757 --> 23:09.261
Yes, you do.

23:09.261 --> 23:10.806
I have calls in to the OPTN
and the U. S. Health Department.

23:10.806 --> 23:12.183
You will not
act until --

23:12.183 --> 23:13.769
Look, do you think I feel
good about this?

23:13.769 --> 23:16.190
I don't.
Nobody does.

23:16.190 --> 23:17.609
But I'm not gonna have
any more patients die

23:17.609 --> 23:18.988
when I could have
done something about it.

23:18.988 --> 23:22.578
So tell your client
that I'm sorry.

23:26.585 --> 23:27.921
It's -- It's not right.

23:27.921 --> 23:29.257
No, it's not.

23:29.257 --> 23:31.136
I will sue them for a fortune,
and I'll win.

23:33.974 --> 23:36.437
Piper will
never live to see it.

23:36.437 --> 23:38.190
[ Door opens ]

23:40.153 --> 23:42.032
Linda: You win.

23:42.032 --> 23:43.993
They're prepping the O. R.
for Meredith's surgery now.

23:43.993 --> 23:45.245
[ Exhales sharply ]

23:45.245 --> 23:47.166
Ah. Thank God.

23:47.166 --> 23:48.501
This isn't
a happy thing, Jonah.

23:48.501 --> 23:50.213
Someone died
because of you.

23:50.213 --> 23:52.300
That's the only reason
the hospital's giving in.

23:52.300 --> 23:53.677
Yeah, but if the hospital
had responded sooner,

23:53.677 --> 23:55.181
that person
would still be alive.

23:55.181 --> 23:57.435
And I've been very clear
about how this works.

23:57.435 --> 23:59.481
Lose the attitude.

23:59.481 --> 24:01.985
[ Handcuffs clicking ]
You got what you want.

24:01.985 --> 24:04.031
Turn the lights
back on.

24:08.581 --> 24:10.084
[ Tablet beeps ]
There.

24:10.084 --> 24:12.923
That should, uh, restore
the lights in, uh,

24:12.923 --> 24:15.469
both the intensive care
and O. R. suites, for now.

24:15.469 --> 24:17.098
The rest of the hospital
is still dark.

24:17.098 --> 24:19.142
But now, I-I need you
to take me to see my wife,

24:19.142 --> 24:20.938
'cause I gotta be there
for the operation,

24:20.938 --> 24:23.734
make sure that you're actually
gonna follow through with it.

24:23.734 --> 24:27.242
♪♪

24:27.242 --> 24:29.161
Well, I guess
we'll be there with you.

24:30.455 --> 24:32.126
[ Handcuffs click ]

24:32.126 --> 24:35.340
♪♪

24:37.468 --> 24:38.930
Hey.

24:38.930 --> 24:41.476
Again,
I'm so, so sor--
Sorry.

24:41.476 --> 24:43.647
I know.

24:46.152 --> 24:50.034
I-I need you
to do something for me.

24:50.034 --> 24:51.579
Anything.

24:51.579 --> 24:53.666
I need to
see the video.

24:53.666 --> 24:55.335
The barrel video?
Yeah.

24:55.335 --> 24:56.964
You've seen it.

24:56.964 --> 24:59.260
Half the lawyers in this
building have seen it, and --

24:59.260 --> 25:01.347
and I haven't.

25:01.347 --> 25:05.146
Lucy, it's...

25:05.146 --> 25:07.150
it's incredibly
hard to watch.

25:07.150 --> 25:09.154
I need to see it.

25:11.658 --> 25:13.369
Okay.

25:26.938 --> 25:28.273
Should I stay, or...

25:28.273 --> 25:29.609
Mnh-mnh.

25:29.609 --> 25:33.491
No. Um...

25:33.491 --> 25:34.743
thank you.

25:43.260 --> 25:44.763
[ Door closes ]

25:57.244 --> 26:00.000
[ <i>Pounds wall</i> ]

26:00.000 --> 26:02.629
[ <i>Inhales shakily</i> ]

26:03.006 --> 26:09.142
♪ <i>Stars shining bright</i>
<i>above you</i> ♪

26:09.142 --> 26:15.403
♪ <i>Night breezes seem to</i>
<i>whisper "I love you"</i> ♪

26:15.403 --> 26:21.540
♪ <i>Birds singing</i>
<i>in the sycamore tree</i> ♪

26:21.540 --> 26:25.464
♪ <i>Dream a little dream of me</i> ♪

26:25.464 --> 26:27.802
Office Nolan will be with you
for every second

26:27.802 --> 26:29.472
of this seven-hour
surgery.

26:29.472 --> 26:32.227
You will not speak to
the surgery team, understood?

26:32.227 --> 26:33.980
You make one move during
any of those seven hours,

26:33.980 --> 26:35.316
we remove you
from the O. R.

26:35.316 --> 26:36.568
and take you straight in
for processing.

26:36.568 --> 26:38.697
Wh--
Of course.

26:38.697 --> 26:40.034
I mean, look, this --

26:40.034 --> 26:42.162
this surgery's gonna
save my wife's life.

26:42.162 --> 26:44.583
Why -- Why would I do
anything to disrupt it?

26:44.583 --> 26:47.966
You do realize you're putting
those doctors under duress.

26:47.966 --> 26:49.718
The both of you,

26:49.718 --> 26:51.889
you're essentially holding
this whole hospital hostage.

26:51.889 --> 26:53.225
Don't listen to that,
sweetheart.

26:53.225 --> 26:54.602
H-How you doing, baby?

26:54.602 --> 26:55.772
Just nervous.

26:55.772 --> 26:58.443
[ Screaming ]

26:59.654 --> 27:01.407
[ Groans ]

27:03.829 --> 27:06.208
Drop it! Stop!
Turn around!

27:06.208 --> 27:07.878
[ Sobbing ]

27:07.878 --> 27:10.257
What were
you thinking?

27:10.257 --> 27:14.808
[ Handcuffs click ]
If she dies,
my daughter doesn't.

27:18.480 --> 27:21.737
Here.
You got what you wanted.

27:21.737 --> 27:24.242
Now bring the hospital
back online.

27:24.242 --> 27:26.496
No.
Why not?

27:26.496 --> 27:28.792
Well, 'cause that's
not how this works.

27:28.792 --> 27:30.545
H-Hey, hey,
watch that.

27:30.545 --> 27:33.092
<i>Mr. Russell, you have a lot of</i>
<i>power right now.</i>

27:33.092 --> 27:35.221
<i>Which is why, despite</i>
<i>my objections, you're here.</i>

27:35.221 --> 27:38.310
<i>But let me make one thing</i>
<i>perfectly clear.</i>

27:38.310 --> 27:40.063
<i>We have work to do.</i>

27:40.063 --> 27:42.944
<i>Your strong-arm tactics</i>
<i>are helping no one.</i>

27:42.944 --> 27:45.198
[ Monitor beeping ]

27:48.579 --> 27:50.082
So, what's gonna happen
to that guy

27:50.082 --> 27:51.795
that tried to
attack Meredith?

27:51.795 --> 27:55.550
He'll be charged with assault,
probably go to prison,

27:55.550 --> 27:57.972
and his daughter will most
likely die while he's in there.

27:57.972 --> 27:59.642
Does that
make you happy?

27:59.642 --> 28:03.023
My wife is getting a second
chance that she really deserves.

28:03.023 --> 28:05.236
That's all I care about.

28:07.073 --> 28:10.246
[ <i>Video game noises</i> ]
He has not looked up from
that thing in an hour.

28:10.246 --> 28:12.082
Oh, come on.
He's just having some fun.

28:12.082 --> 28:14.253
[ Chuckles ]
I hope this is
not your attitude

28:14.253 --> 28:16.590
when it comes to
our child's screen time.

28:16.590 --> 28:18.261
What attitude?

28:18.261 --> 28:21.099
I'm just saying, there's nothing
with a little gaming.

28:21.099 --> 28:22.518
I like gaming.

28:22.518 --> 28:24.982
Yeah, you like
gaming a little too much.

28:24.982 --> 28:26.484
[ Chuckles ]

28:26.484 --> 28:28.363
I don't feel good.

28:28.363 --> 28:30.241
What's wrong?

28:33.038 --> 28:35.209
My head hurts.

28:36.963 --> 28:39.216
Let me see.

28:39.216 --> 28:40.761
His pupils are
two different sizes.

28:40.761 --> 28:42.556
That is a sign
of a serious head injury.

28:42.556 --> 28:44.143
Can you go
get the doctor?

28:44.143 --> 28:46.564
Hey, Rory,
w-what happened?

28:46.564 --> 28:48.567
Did you hit your head?

28:48.567 --> 28:51.741
I think so.
I don't remember.

28:51.741 --> 28:54.872
Rory!
Are you okay?

28:54.872 --> 28:56.249
Oh, my baby.

28:56.249 --> 28:57.835
Hi, Mom.
Hi.

28:57.835 --> 28:59.546
My head really hurts.

28:59.546 --> 29:00.925
Oh.
Come on.

29:00.925 --> 29:02.427
Let's get you home.
It's fine. Come on.

29:02.427 --> 29:03.931
Uh, actually, sorry.

29:03.931 --> 29:07.561
I-I know you don't know me, but
he has a serious head injury.

29:07.561 --> 29:09.065
That's okay.
Nothing an ice pack can't fix.

29:09.065 --> 29:10.317
Right, buddy?

29:10.317 --> 29:11.569
N-No, I don't --
I don't think --

29:11.569 --> 29:13.031
Hold on.
Let me take a look at him.

29:16.871 --> 29:19.000
Your son is showing signs
of a concussion.

29:19.000 --> 29:20.963
We're having some issues
with our equipment right now,

29:20.963 --> 29:22.465
but it's important
Rory stay

29:22.465 --> 29:24.593
until we can run some tests on
him, make sure his head's okay.

29:24.593 --> 29:25.679
No, we're
taking him home.
Come on, baby.

29:25.679 --> 29:27.641
Sir, I really think --
Rory is fine.

29:27.641 --> 29:29.019
Kids play.
These things happen.

29:29.019 --> 29:30.689
He just needs a little bit
of rest, is all.

29:30.689 --> 29:31.984
Sir, you don't understand.

29:31.984 --> 29:33.568
It's possible
there could be fluid

29:33.568 --> 29:34.947
putting pressure
on his brain.

29:34.947 --> 29:36.826
He could go to sleep
and never wake up.

29:36.826 --> 29:38.328
Thank you, but we don't
need the kind of help

29:38.328 --> 29:39.580
that you offer here.

29:39.580 --> 29:41.084
It's against
our beliefs.

29:41.084 --> 29:43.004
I-I'm sorry, beliefs?
D-Did you not hear him?

29:43.004 --> 29:44.673
H-He could
have a skull fracture.

29:44.673 --> 29:46.928
Okay, we believe that
the only care Rory needs

29:46.928 --> 29:48.556
is the healing power
of prayer.

29:48.556 --> 29:50.726
Listen, folks, maybe you should
just hear the doctor out.

29:50.726 --> 29:52.604
I'm sorry, but why are
you two butting in?

29:52.604 --> 29:53.983
You're not
his parents.

29:53.983 --> 29:55.569
Okay, you -- you have to
do something here.

29:55.569 --> 29:56.947
I can't.
I don't have the authority.

29:56.947 --> 29:58.616
But I do.

29:58.616 --> 30:01.748
I have probably cause
to take your son into
protective custody,

30:01.748 --> 30:05.296
according to Section 300 of the
Welfare and Institution Code.

30:05.296 --> 30:07.008
Excuse me?
That's not happening.

30:07.008 --> 30:08.886
Yeah, it is, and if you try
to interfere,

30:08.886 --> 30:12.059
I have the authority to put you
both under custody as well.

30:12.059 --> 30:14.063
We're gonna go
call our lawyer.

30:14.063 --> 30:16.943
We'll be right out in the hall,
okay, Rory?

30:18.445 --> 30:20.282
We'll be right back,
okay?

30:22.703 --> 30:24.165
Listen, just
hang here with the doc.

30:24.165 --> 30:25.877
He'll take care of you,
okay?

30:26.920 --> 30:29.716
Hey, where -- where is the
heart? When is it coming?

30:29.716 --> 30:32.347
Not until your wife is fully
anesthetized and prepped.

30:33.809 --> 30:36.687
[ <i>Clears throat</i> ]
<i>Y-You're doing great, honey.</i>

30:36.687 --> 30:39.485
Don't worry, okay?
You're doing so well.

30:39.485 --> 30:41.572
<i>I love you so much.</i>

30:41.572 --> 30:43.493
<i>I love you, too.</i>

30:43.493 --> 30:45.914
<i>Meredith, there's someone else</i>
<i>you should talk to</i>

30:45.914 --> 30:48.001
<i>before your surgery.</i>

30:48.001 --> 30:49.379
<i>This is Piper.</i>

30:49.379 --> 30:51.258
<i>W-Wait.</i>
<i>Don't. Don't.</i>

30:51.258 --> 30:53.011
<i>It's her heart</i>
<i>you're taking.</i>

30:53.011 --> 30:55.056
<i>D-Don't.</i>
<i>Stop that.</i>

30:55.056 --> 30:57.018
Jonah.
Jonah, it's okay.

30:57.979 --> 31:00.734
Listening to her
is the least I can do.

31:00.734 --> 31:03.865
<i>Thank you. I've spent</i>
<i>the last 20 minutes</i>

31:03.865 --> 31:05.952
<i>trying to come up with</i>
<i>the right words to say.</i>

31:05.952 --> 31:10.002
My dad thinks I can convince you
by telling you who I am.

31:10.002 --> 31:13.340
As if where I want to
go to college

31:13.340 --> 31:15.344
or what I want to
do with my life

31:15.344 --> 31:17.223
will somehow make you
give me that heart.

31:17.223 --> 31:19.519
<i>But he doesn't understand</i>
<i>how scared you are,</i>

31:19.519 --> 31:22.107
<i>how long you've been</i>
<i>living with that fear.</i>

31:22.107 --> 31:23.861
From the moment they
told you there was

31:23.861 --> 31:25.990
something wrong
with your heart,

31:25.990 --> 31:28.703
you've been terrified
of the day it will stop.

31:28.703 --> 31:33.462
My dad can't understand that
because he's not dying.

31:33.462 --> 31:35.174
<i>Like we are.</i>

31:36.718 --> 31:40.516
[ <i>Voice breaking</i> ] <i>So even</i>
<i>though I'm not ready to go,</i>

31:40.516 --> 31:44.566
<i>not ready to</i>
<i>leave my dad alone...</i>

31:44.566 --> 31:47.822
<i>I forgive you</i>
<i>for what you're doing.</i>

31:47.822 --> 31:50.369
Don't -- Don't...

31:50.369 --> 31:51.956
<i>Don't listen to her,</i>
<i>Mere.</i>

31:51.956 --> 31:54.418
Jonah,
I can't do this.

31:54.418 --> 31:55.964
I'm sorry.
I'm sorry.

31:55.964 --> 31:57.298
Please stop.
Just stop.

31:57.298 --> 31:59.261
<i>W-What are you doing?</i>
<i>Don't -- Don't stop.</i>

31:59.261 --> 32:01.473
<i>The patient withdrew</i>
<i>her consent.</i>

32:01.473 --> 32:03.937
<i>I don't</i>
<i>want to lose you.</i>

32:03.937 --> 32:06.482
Please. Please.
I'm sorry.

32:06.482 --> 32:08.695
<i>I'm proud of you,</i>
<i>Piper.</i>

32:08.695 --> 32:10.490
<i>We'll see you here in</i>
<i>a little while, okay?</i>

32:10.490 --> 32:14.455
♪♪

32:14.455 --> 32:16.919
It's over, Jonah.

32:16.919 --> 32:18.422
Turn off
the ransomware.

32:18.422 --> 32:20.509
No one else
needs to die today.

32:23.181 --> 32:24.641
Jonah.

32:24.641 --> 32:26.312
[ Sniffles ]

32:26.312 --> 32:27.605
It's over.

32:30.111 --> 32:31.865
[ Sighs ]

32:39.378 --> 32:42.633
[ Tablet beeps ]

32:42.633 --> 32:45.932
I'm --
I-I can't get in.

32:45.932 --> 32:48.813
They --
They locked me out.

32:48.813 --> 32:51.025
Who did?

32:51.025 --> 32:52.694
My partners.

32:52.694 --> 32:54.031
I thought they were
trying to help me

32:54.031 --> 32:56.035
out of the goodness
of their heart.

32:56.035 --> 32:58.081
[ Electricity powers down ]

32:58.081 --> 33:01.419
But they just used me.

33:01.419 --> 33:02.839
To get paid.

33:02.839 --> 33:09.017
♪♪

33:12.440 --> 33:15.154
You think I crossed a line
taking custody of Rory.

33:15.154 --> 33:17.574
Police should not
be empowered

33:17.574 --> 33:18.911
to take a child
from their parents

33:18.911 --> 33:20.497
without any kind
of due process.

33:20.497 --> 33:22.000
Did you not just see
the mountain of paperwork

33:22.000 --> 33:23.378
I just filled out?

33:23.378 --> 33:25.424
Indigenous children,
Black and brown children,

33:25.424 --> 33:28.095
the law has a history
of separating families.

33:28.095 --> 33:29.765
But this was an emergency.

33:29.765 --> 33:32.478
I mean, I-I feared for
the safety of this child,

33:32.478 --> 33:35.275
and I will not apologize
for protecting him.

33:35.275 --> 33:37.947
I know. I know why
you did what you did.

33:37.947 --> 33:40.911
But cops have always found
a way to justify their actions,

33:40.911 --> 33:42.790
whether warranted
or not.

33:42.790 --> 33:44.835
[ Cellphone ringing ]

33:44.835 --> 33:46.714
Hello?

33:46.714 --> 33:47.841
Harper, you still
with the kid?

33:47.841 --> 33:49.677
Yeah, we're waiting
for his doctor.

33:49.677 --> 33:52.516
Listen, I sent your JCR
paperwork to Systems.

33:52.516 --> 33:56.190
It came back having no record
of a Griffin and Gabby Kane

33:56.190 --> 33:59.070
ever having a child at
a hospital or via adoption.

33:59.070 --> 34:00.490
What?

34:00.490 --> 34:02.367
Not only that,
there's no birth certificate

34:02.367 --> 34:06.000
or social security number
on file for a Rory Kane.

34:06.000 --> 34:07.586
Those people
aren't his parents.

34:09.841 --> 34:12.136
Lisa, the boy's parents,
the Kanes,

34:12.136 --> 34:13.514
a-are they still
in the waiting area?

34:13.514 --> 34:15.476
Uh, no, they left about
20 minutes ago.

34:17.355 --> 34:18.690
But you can't do this.

34:18.690 --> 34:20.652
I mean, my wife needs me.
I've got to take care of her.

34:20.652 --> 34:21.988
It's too late
for that.

34:21.988 --> 34:23.366
You're headed to jail
on a murder charge.

34:23.366 --> 34:24.702
If the hospital
can't pay the ransom

34:24.702 --> 34:25.955
and get the power
turned back on,

34:25.955 --> 34:27.374
that means Piper
can't get her heart,

34:27.374 --> 34:28.794
and that'll
be two deaths on you.

34:28.794 --> 34:30.087
Unless you tell us
who you're working with

34:30.087 --> 34:31.673
so we can end this
in time to save her.

34:31.673 --> 34:34.721
Look, Meredith still has some
time left to live.

34:34.721 --> 34:37.226
If you cooperate,
it is possible

34:37.226 --> 34:39.981
you could get out on bail
and spend that time with her.

34:43.738 --> 34:46.118
Alright, Spencer Murkle
and Chloe Speeker.

34:46.118 --> 34:47.745
I met them both online.

34:47.745 --> 34:50.292
They were offering some
money for me to be able
to build some ransomware.

34:50.292 --> 34:51.627
I-I've got
all this medical debt.

34:51.627 --> 34:54.216
So I said yes,

34:54.216 --> 34:57.138
but they were the ones who
suggested hacking the hospital.

34:57.138 --> 34:59.559
And I-I thought it was actually
gonna help Meredith and I,

34:59.559 --> 35:02.440
but clearly, we were
just a means to an end.

35:02.440 --> 35:04.193
And where can we
find them?

35:04.193 --> 35:07.407
I don't know, but, uh, I mean,
your tech team

35:07.407 --> 35:09.996
could probably trace
those messages.

35:09.996 --> 35:15.172
♪♪

35:15.172 --> 35:16.549
7-Adam-100 to units
in the rear.

35:16.549 --> 35:18.011
Is the C-Side set?

35:18.011 --> 35:19.388
Woman: <i>C-Side is set.</i>

35:19.388 --> 35:21.559
Roger.
Making contact.

35:21.559 --> 35:27.070
♪♪

35:27.070 --> 35:28.740
[ Knock on door ]

35:28.740 --> 35:30.493
Police!
We have a warrant!

35:30.493 --> 35:32.038
Open the door now!

35:33.539 --> 35:36.003
♪ Where is it now? ♪

35:36.003 --> 35:37.924
♪ Where has it been? ♪

35:37.924 --> 35:39.176
Clear.

35:39.176 --> 35:41.179
♪ Where is it now? ♪

35:41.179 --> 35:42.014
♪ Where has it been? ♪

35:42.014 --> 35:43.475
Clear.

35:43.475 --> 35:45.814
♪ Where is it now? ♪

35:45.814 --> 35:47.191
This place is deserted.

35:47.191 --> 35:49.112
Looks like no one's
been in here in months.

35:49.112 --> 35:50.530
Our trace
must have been off.

35:50.530 --> 35:52.075
There's no
computer equipment here.

35:52.075 --> 35:53.912
You can't run that kind
of cyber attack from a laptop.

36:00.800 --> 36:03.304
[ Helicopter blades whirring ]

36:03.304 --> 36:12.572
♪♪

36:12.572 --> 36:21.840
♪♪

36:21.840 --> 36:28.811
♪♪

36:28.811 --> 36:35.866
♪♪

36:35.866 --> 36:42.838
♪♪

36:42.838 --> 36:45.008
Hi. Keep your hands
where we can see them.

36:45.008 --> 36:46.677
What's this about?

36:46.677 --> 36:48.181
It's about which one of you
wants to disable

36:48.181 --> 36:49.683
the ransomware
and make a deal,

36:49.683 --> 36:52.564
and which one of you
is gonna spend a couple
decades in prison.

36:54.526 --> 36:56.781
That's a good answer.

36:56.781 --> 37:01.123
♪♪

37:01.123 --> 37:03.710
[ Siren chirps ]

37:03.710 --> 37:06.340
Hey!
Show me your hands.

37:06.340 --> 37:08.678
[ Breathing heavily ]

37:08.678 --> 37:10.974
We were coming back to
the hospital to get Rory.

37:10.974 --> 37:12.727
Sure you were.

37:12.727 --> 37:15.524
Put your hands over your head,
interlace your fingers.

37:15.524 --> 37:17.570
You're under arrest
for kidnapping.

37:20.074 --> 37:21.744
We gave Rory
a good home.

37:21.744 --> 37:23.372
Gabby,
don't say anything.

37:23.372 --> 37:25.293
[ Handcuffs clicking ]

37:25.293 --> 37:30.260
♪♪

37:33.558 --> 37:36.022
She's been
in there forever.
Yeah.

37:36.022 --> 37:38.902
I tried knocking,
but she didn't answer.

37:38.902 --> 37:40.654
We should check on her.

37:40.654 --> 37:41.782
[ Knock on door ]

37:41.782 --> 37:43.828
Lucy?
It's Chris and Tamara.

37:43.828 --> 37:45.247
We're coming in.

37:51.133 --> 37:54.014
Lucy, are you okay?

37:54.014 --> 37:56.476
Oh. Sorry.

37:56.476 --> 37:59.273
I-I've been processing
a few things.

37:59.273 --> 38:02.404
You watched it?

38:02.404 --> 38:04.575
Yeah.

38:04.575 --> 38:06.370
Every minute.

38:06.370 --> 38:08.123
Maybe we should
go home.

38:08.123 --> 38:09.626
Yeah.

38:09.626 --> 38:13.300
Um, I've decided
not to testify.

38:13.300 --> 38:15.136
I completely understand.

38:15.136 --> 38:17.182
I've been trying to prove
how strong I am,

38:17.182 --> 38:21.190
but...I survived that.

38:21.190 --> 38:23.193
I don't have
anything to prove.

38:24.487 --> 38:25.782
Yeah.

38:25.782 --> 38:27.995
We have
plenty of evidence.

38:27.995 --> 38:29.664
We'll convict her without you,
I promise.

38:29.664 --> 38:31.668
Let's go.
I'm making you dinner.

38:31.668 --> 38:34.423
Okay.
Is it another ClipTalk recipe?

38:34.423 --> 38:35.633
No.

38:35.633 --> 38:36.928
ClipTalk has recipes?

38:36.928 --> 38:38.639
No, it has gimmicks.

38:38.639 --> 38:40.893
And yet,
you cleaned the plate.

38:40.893 --> 38:41.937
Dude.

38:41.937 --> 38:43.148
Sorry.

38:43.148 --> 38:44.400
[ Chuckles ]

38:44.400 --> 38:47.114
Hey.
Uh, headed out?

38:47.114 --> 38:48.658
I am.

38:48.658 --> 38:50.077
Me, too.

38:50.077 --> 38:51.831
You know, Tamara was
just talking about

38:51.831 --> 38:54.210
how she really wanted to try
one of the restaurants

38:54.210 --> 38:55.504
in the neighborhood.

38:55.504 --> 38:57.216
Is -- Is there a place
you recommend?

38:57.216 --> 38:59.553
Uh, there's this great vegan
joint around the corner.

38:59.553 --> 39:01.140
Uh. The Great Gaia.

39:01.140 --> 39:02.935
Earth-friendly,
cruelty-free.

39:02.935 --> 39:05.315
I could show you the way.

39:05.315 --> 39:06.777
You okay?

39:06.777 --> 39:09.280
G-- Yeah. Go.
[ Chuckles ]

39:10.449 --> 39:12.244
I'll make her dinner.

39:12.244 --> 39:13.663
Let's go.

39:13.663 --> 39:15.459
I just gotta
get my stuff.

39:15.459 --> 39:18.547
♪ And the neon light
paints the outside ♪

39:18.547 --> 39:19.967
You cook?

39:19.967 --> 39:21.387
God, no.

39:21.387 --> 39:23.557
Eat out,
or order in?

39:23.557 --> 39:24.977
Depends.

39:24.977 --> 39:27.356
Are you gonna rub my feet
if we order in?

39:27.356 --> 39:28.984
[ Scoffs ] I'll rub them
at the restaurant.

39:28.984 --> 39:31.572
I don't care.
What? That is gross.

39:31.572 --> 39:33.243
They're your feet.

39:33.243 --> 39:35.914
Do I really have to explain
to you when it is appropriate

39:35.914 --> 39:37.668
to take off your shoes
in a public place

39:37.668 --> 39:41.466
when it is <i>not</i>
the beach or the park?

39:41.466 --> 39:43.971
So you're saying
never on an airplane?

39:43.971 --> 39:45.975
Oh, now I know you're
just messing with me.

39:45.975 --> 39:47.644
[ Chuckles ]
What?

39:47.644 --> 39:50.150
♪ Dream ♪

39:50.150 --> 39:52.696
I just wanna go home.

39:52.696 --> 39:54.365
♪ I grew up so overwhelmed ♪

39:54.365 --> 39:57.580
Uh, yeah, I'm afraid
that can't happen.

39:57.580 --> 39:59.877
My mom and dad
can explain.

39:59.877 --> 40:03.048
Um...
[ Sighs ]

40:03.048 --> 40:06.848
I'm so sorry, but...

40:06.848 --> 40:09.770
they are
not your real parents.

40:09.770 --> 40:16.783
Um, you were kidnapped
when you were three years old.

40:16.783 --> 40:18.787
I know -- I know this must be
hard for you to hear,

40:18.787 --> 40:22.210
but your real name is --
is Scott Reynolds.

40:22.210 --> 40:24.380
Your parents are
Gerald and Dorothy.

40:24.380 --> 40:27.303
They, um --
They're on their way here now.

40:27.303 --> 40:32.062
They sent me
a picture to show you.

40:32.062 --> 40:35.235
So, that is Gerald,
and that is Dorothy,

40:35.235 --> 40:37.989
and that little, handsome guy
right there is you.

40:37.989 --> 40:42.164
What if I don't
want to go with them?

40:42.164 --> 40:43.793
I don't even know them.

40:43.793 --> 40:48.300
Listen, I-I know this all must
be moving very fast for you,

40:48.300 --> 40:52.977
but...
until they get here,

40:52.977 --> 40:56.274
I will sit here
and wait with you.

40:56.274 --> 40:58.486
We both will.

40:58.486 --> 41:00.658
And while we do, um,

41:00.658 --> 41:02.996
can you show me that
game you were playing?

41:02.996 --> 41:05.959
'Cause I think
my boys will dig it.

41:05.959 --> 41:07.128
Sure.

41:07.128 --> 41:08.463
♪ And I'll try to do it, too ♪

41:08.463 --> 41:12.723
♪ Use words
to grade my pictures blue ♪

41:12.723 --> 41:14.182
♪ And I hope
they'll take you, too ♪

41:14.182 --> 41:17.022
[ <i>Video game noises</i> ]

41:17.022 --> 41:21.363
Well, the doctor is very happy
with how the surgery went.

41:21.363 --> 41:23.199
The next 48 hours
will be critical,

41:23.199 --> 41:27.207
but she thinks that Piper has an
excellent chance at a long life.

41:27.207 --> 41:28.878
And her dad?

41:28.878 --> 41:31.090
Oh, I don't the D. A.'s office
is gonna press charges.

41:31.090 --> 41:33.093
Even if they did,
there's no jury in the world

41:33.093 --> 41:35.056
would convict him.

41:35.056 --> 41:36.308
What about Meredith?

41:36.308 --> 41:38.270
She is on her way
to hospice care.

41:38.270 --> 41:42.820
Sadly, she does
not have much time left.

41:42.820 --> 41:46.703
Well, I have heard on hard days,
the only prescription

41:46.703 --> 41:49.291
is a hot bath
and a cold glass of wine.

41:49.291 --> 41:50.710
Really?

41:50.710 --> 41:52.546
I've never been much of
a bath guy.

41:52.546 --> 41:54.300
Even if you
take it with me?

41:54.300 --> 41:57.598
Oh, that is an entirely
different kind of prescription.

41:57.598 --> 42:00.061
Mm.

42:00.061 --> 42:01.647
As soon as you
take a shower.

42:01.647 --> 42:04.946
I will have you know,
this smell was hard-earned

42:04.946 --> 42:08.786
by transporting 27 patients out
of and back into this hospital.

42:08.786 --> 42:11.959
Yeah, no, and I will be happy to
reward all that hard work

42:11.959 --> 42:13.461
with some quality
naked time,

42:13.461 --> 42:16.633
just as soon as you
scrub those pits.

42:16.633 --> 42:21.309
♪ Oooooh ♪

42:21.309 --> 42:22.688
[ Sniffs, chuckles ]

